<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,259,644]" box="[151,630,259,285]" pageId="13" pageNumber="54">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,630,259,285]" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="13" pageNumber="54" reason="2">
<taxonomicName authority="Vogt, 1909" authorityName="Vogt" authorityYear="1909" box="[151,630,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Bombus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="mendax" subSpecies="latofasciatus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,630,259,285]" pageId="13" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,498,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="54">Bombus mendax latofasciatus</emphasis>
Vogt, 1909
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,259,644]" pageId="13" pageNumber="54">
It is a mountain declining subspecies, spread in the Pyrenees and the Cantabrian Range, between 
<date pageId="13" pageNumber="54" value="1400" valueMax="2150">
1400 and 
<quantity box="[151,207,332,357]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.15" pageId="13" pageNumber="54" unit="m" value="2150.0">2150</quantity>
</date>
m (
<figureCitation box="[252,320,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1517,1539]" captionTargetBox="[152,1437,877,1496]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1437,877,1496]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 7. Distribution (in meters) range of the bumblebee species and subspecies observed in contemporary samplings (grey rectangles) in the Pyrenees compared with the known altitude distribution (black bars) from historical data." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322695/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="54">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Ornosa" box="[343,689,332,357]" pageId="13" pageNumber="54" refString="Ornosa, C. &amp; Ortiz-Sanchez, F. J. (2004) Hymenoptera: Apoidea I. In: Consejo Superior de Investigaciones Cientificas (Ed.), Fauna Iberica. Fol. 23. Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales, CSIC, Madrid, pp. 1 - 556." type="book chapter" year="2004">Ornosa &amp; Ortiz-Sánchez 2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Santamaria" box="[701,958,332,357]" pageId="13" pageNumber="54" refString="Santamaria, S., Castro L., Garcia-Camacho, R., Gimenez, L., Mendez, M., Milla, R., Teixido, A. L. &amp; Torices, R. (2011) Abejorros (Bombus spp.: Hymenoptera, Apidae) del Jou de Los Cabrones (Parque Nacional Picos De Europa) y confirmacion de la Presencia de Bombus mendax Gerstaecker, 1869 en la Cordillera Cantabrica (Espana). Boletin de la Sociedad Entomologica Aragonesa, 48, 143 - 146." type="journal article" year="2011">
Santamaría 
<emphasis box="[834,891,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="54">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
). In the past, 69 individuals were recorded (
<bibRefCitation author="Ornosa" box="[158,542,368,392]" pageId="13" pageNumber="54" refString="Ornosa, C. (1984) La subfamilia Bombinae (Hym., Apidae) de la fauna espanola. Coleccion Tesis Doctorales, n ° 203 / 84, Ed. Universidad Complutense de Madrid, Madrid, 334 pp." type="book" year="1984">Ornosa 1984; Castro pers. comm.</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="54" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,259,644]" pageId="13" pageNumber="54">
<taxonomicName box="[199,469,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Bombus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="mendax" subSpecies="latofasciatus">
<emphasis box="[199,469,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="54">B. mendax latofasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a very rare (
<figureCitation box="[641,709,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1760,1782]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,1156,1718]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[150,1436,1146,1726]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 3. Map showing historical locations (●) and recent records (*) of Bombus mendax latofasciatus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322691/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="54">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) and threatened subspecies (
<tableCitation box="[1034,1122,404,429]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,239,152,175]" captionTargetBox="[159,1394,332,1883]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="TABLE 2. Bumblebee species and subspecies collected in the Pyrenees and IUCN category ranks (from Spain: Verdú &amp; Galante (2006), Verdú et al. (2011) and from Europe: Rasmont et al. (2015): Not Evaluated, NE; Endangered, EN; Vulnerable, VU; Data Deficient, DD; Least Concern, LC) of the extant bumblebee species and subspecies in the Pyrenees. The number of individuals sampled between 2006 and 2015 is indicated. In rare species and those with relevant records, the number of individuals known from historical literature or collections is included in brackets." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/BDBE6627FF98FFBFFF3CFF45FADEFED5" pageId="13" pageNumber="54" tableUuid="BDBE6627FF98FFBFFF3CFF45FADEFED5">Table 2</tableCitation>
), only collected once in the last eight years in the Pyrenees, in the National Park Aigüestortes and St. Maurici lake (Ornosa &amp; Torres 2009) and in the Cantabrian Range (Picos de Europa), where 15 individuals were collected in July, 2008 (
<collectingRegion box="[1288,1386,476,501]" country="Spain" name="Asturias" pageId="13" pageNumber="54">Asturias</collectingRegion>
, the Bastards, Jou) (
<bibRefCitation author="Santamaria" box="[323,579,511,536]" pageId="13" pageNumber="54" refString="Santamaria, S., Castro L., Garcia-Camacho, R., Gimenez, L., Mendez, M., Milla, R., Teixido, A. L. &amp; Torices, R. (2011) Abejorros (Bombus spp.: Hymenoptera, Apidae) del Jou de Los Cabrones (Parque Nacional Picos De Europa) y confirmacion de la Presencia de Bombus mendax Gerstaecker, 1869 en la Cordillera Cantabrica (Espana). Boletin de la Sociedad Entomologica Aragonesa, 48, 143 - 146." type="journal article" year="2011">
Santamaría 
<emphasis box="[457,513,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="54">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
). It was assessed as Endangered (EN) in the 
<collectionCode box="[1074,1142,512,536]" pageId="13" pageNumber="54">IUCN</collectionCode>
Spanish Red List (Ornosa &amp; Torres 2009).
</paragraph>
